      <title>THREE-DIMENSIONAL OBJECTS FROM THE ENVIRONMENT</title>
      <para id="id1370596">Activity 1: </para>
      <para id="id1170488086544">To investigate and compare three-dimensional objects from the environment according to geometrical properties by making three-dimensional models using cut-out polygons</para>
      <para id="id1170475832436">[LO 2.1, 3.2, 3.4, 3.5, 4.8]</para>
      <para id="id1170486861731">1. Investigating nets: boxes.</para>
      <para id="id5497496">You need a cornflake box, a box that contained tea and other boxes. Carefully open the boxes where they were glued so that they can be laid flat on the table. Examine the plan or net of the box.</para>
      <para id="id1170481485023">2. Before you cut out the net below, fill in the dots for a dice on each face. Then cut out the net, fold it into a cube and stick it with sticky tape. Look at a real dice to see if your numbers are correct.</para>
