      <para id="id2915170">Activity 4:</para>
      <para id="id8530248">To investigate and approximate volume of three-dimensional objects [LO 4.8]</para>
      <list id="id1170485427915" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>You may work in groups. Each group will need: various small boxes, e.g. a matchbox; a rectangular container for margarine; a shoebox, etc. (try to have five of them); sugar cubes (or 1 cm wooden cubes from the Foundation Phase).</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id7110021">1. Pack sugar cubes into the matchbox and fill it with the cubes. How many do you need?</para>
      <para id="id7738264"/>
      <para id="id1170486858468">2. Now do the same with the other boxes and complete the table below:</para>
